cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.LG 

This paper deals with natural language processing methods for extracting keywords from online communication data to characterize social relationships. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves social network analysis, which suggests the category cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The use of machine learning techniques for keyword extraction could also place the paper in the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it in the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves human assessments of the extracted keywords, which could suggest the category cs.SI (Social and Information Systems).
